However, farming in darkness will also face visual limitation, leading to the extension of farming time. Lan said: "Because of the lack of light, the planting may not be on a straight line, so I wear a headlight to cultivate."

Although the working hours were stretched, Lan showed that it would continue.

Another 62 -year -old Vietnamese farmer also said that he had changed the farming time to the evening and early morning. He said: "Although it can be seen clearly during the day, but the temperature is too high, the work process will become uncomfortable, and it will be tired."

Fortunately, farmers choosing to farm at night will not affect the income and expenditure efficiency. They can still earn about $ 40 a day (about S $ 54). Compared with the labor class with a revenue of only 250 US dollars per income, the income of farmers is relatively considerable.

